Here's a refined version of the email that acknowledges their effort:

Subject: Continued Collaboration and Heartfelt Thanks

Dear [Client's Name],

I hope you are doing well.

I am writing to let you know that I have decided to withdraw my resignation from [Your Organization] and will be continuing to contribute to our project.

I sincerely appreciate the tremendous support you have shown during this time. I am truly grateful for your efforts in accommodating all the requirements to ensure my retention. Your support and encouragement have meant a lot to me, and I am excited to continue our collaboration and work towards the success of our project.

Thank you once again for everything.

Warm regards,
[Your Name]
[Your Title]
[Your Contact Information]

Would you like me to make it sound even better?

